news.title: Maharashtra to finish mapping of rural land with drones by March-end
news.para: The Union government had allocated 25 drones to the Maharashtra land records department, which comes under the settlement commissioner’s office, last year for speeding up the land survey project, which was launched to create accurate land records for rural planning and reduce property disputes.

news.title: Ludhiana Improvement Trust in dock over 'non-construction charge'
news.para: Quashing the demand for non-construction charges of Rs 1,57,000 along with incidental or consequential penalties, the District Consumer Disputes Redressal Commission, Ludhiana ordered LIT to pay composite compensation of Rs 10,000 to the complainant, Harjinder Singh of Rajguru Nagar.

news.title: Call on NA tax on housing societies in February 2023: Maharashtra Revenue Minister
news.para: All properties, including housing societies, falling under the ‘gaothan’ areas, as classified by the collector in accordance with the Maharashtra Land Revenue Code, 1960, have to pay the NA tax.

news.title: Chandigarh: Sector 53 housing scheme too leaves out middle class with 'out-of-reach' pricing
news.para: The recent Supreme Court judgement freezing the floor area ratio has further raised doubts whether the government agency will be able to lower its prices for the new proposed inventory.

news.title: In land acquisition matters, even tenant needs to be heard before issuance of final declaration: Karnataka HC
news.para: On June 9,2016, a gazette notification was issued for acquisition of these land for establishment of a Rehabilitation Centre vis-a-vis a result of execution of Hippargi dam Project.

news.title: Estate office's slipup caused Rs 9.4 crore loss in Chandigarh: CAG
news.para: The UT administration had leased out government built shops (SCOs)/booths in Sector 17-E in 1960s and 1970s for a period of five years.

news.title: Delhi: MCD receives property tax of Rs 55.37 crore under SAMRIDDHI scheme
news.para: Under this scheme, property owners of authorised and regularised colonies can settle all property tax related liabilities by paying property tax of the residential properties for the current year and previous five years.

news.title: Delhi HC pulls up authorities over property records going missing from government office
news.para: ​The high court said the function of the sub-registrars is to register various documents related to assets of the citizens and it cannot be treated in a "cavalier and negligent manner".

news.title: Goa government to amend land revenue code for stone crushing units
news.para: This would be applicable for activities involving basalt or stone crushing units as they are essential for various developmental works, and will be applicable to those that have been operating legally as of December 31, 2007.

news.title: Mohali development body gives nod to revised layout plan for colony
news.para: The promoter company, Curo India Private Limited requested Gmada to approve the revised layout plan, which was sent to the office of the chief town planner, Punjab for technical approval.

news.title: Mysuru: Khata registration drive launched in Chamarajanagar district
news.para: Of the 24,897 properties, only 9,620 have khata registration done under CMC limits. They had also obtained the necessary digitally signed form-3 khata copy, which was issued by CMC, department of revenue, stamps and registration after verifying the property documents of these property holders.

news.title: Lucknow: Residents seek defence minister's help for revamp of LDA houses
news.para: Residents of Tilaknagar, who largely hail from the Jatav community, claimed that the homes were now unsuitable to live in as they have developed cracks and walls were crumbling down.

news.title: Goa: Another 90 days to file applications for regularising homes
news.para: The cabinet granted approval to amend the Goa Regularisation of Unauthorised Construction Act, 2016 to receive fresh applications to regularise houses.

news.title: In 15 days, over 2,700 properties of tax defaulters sealed in Ahmedabad
news.para: The civic body has prepared a list of about 50,000 such properties where the tax dues are exceeding Rs 50,000. The civic body has sealed 7,704 properties so far this financial year.

news.title: Nashik civic body issues fresh warrants to 80 property tax defaulters
news.para: According to an official from the civic body, the NMC will confiscate the properties concerned if the defaulters fail to pay the tax. Last month, the NMC had served first notice to these defaulters giving them a deadline of 15-days, but that did not seem to work.
